OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1772121848
OL,3,CBus drivers continue 10-day walkout on
OL,4,Cthe Isle of Man
OL,6,FShe said: "We will not move if they
OL,7,Fdon't come back with anything. This
OL,8,Fwill take as long as it takes, and
OL,9,Fthey ain't moving."
OL,11,FWhen asked why drivers feel the need
OL,12,Fto strike, Debbie said: "Our members
OL,13,Fwork between 40 and 45 hours a week.
OL,14,FThey get a flat rate whether that be
OL,15,Fon a bank holiday, night working,
OL,16,Fweekend working - days where people
OL,17,Fwould like to spend time with their
OL,18,Ffamily - they get a flat rate.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/5
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,394,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F393A1772121848
OL,3,CBus drivers continue 10-day walkout on
OL,4,Cthe Isle of Man
OL,6,FThe strike started on Saturday 21
OL,7,FFebruary and is scheduled to last
OL,8,Funtil Tuesday 3 March.
OL,10,F"Strike is a last resort. We have been
OL,11,Ftrying to have constructive dialogue
OL,12,Fwith many many years. There's some of
OL,13,Four members who've worked for a long
OL,14,Fperiod of time.
OL,16,F"There's (other) people out there who
OL,17,Fare getting much more pay, and they're
OL,18,Fgoing to start losing the very good,
OL,19,Fexperienced, skilled workers, because
OL,20,Fthey've had enough."
OL,26,@xD@JpmxD@Ppn
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/5
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
